 ('56', '27', '3', '1', 'en_us', '5', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Staff\",\"slug\":\"staff\",\"postDate\":1458873960,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"5\",\"fields\":{\"5\":{\"28\":{\"type\":\"secondaryHero\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Staff\",\"body\":\"<p>Our instructors have spent many years perfecting the martial arts craft and continue to go through extensive testing training and certifications to ensure that we are able to provide our students with the best care and instruction. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Here, we\\u2019re family and we truly enjoy what we do and we enjoy sharing that passion with others. Collectively we invest in each student, as we feel that their success is our success!&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"contactButton\":\"1\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#000000\",\"backgroundImage\":[\"41\"],\"mapTitle\":\"\",\"mapContent\":\"\",\"mapAddress\":\"\",\"flexibleArea\":\"\"}},\"29\":{\"type\":\"staff\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"64\"],\"staffName\":\"Steve Sosa\",\"staffTitle\":\"Instructor, 7th degree black belt\",\"body\":\"<p>Master Steve Sosa has been an unstoppable, highly skilled martial artist for over 30 years. Master Sosa a 7th degree black belt in karate, trained by legendary martial artists such as Tim Kirby, Allen Steen, Ray McCallum, Billye Jackson, and Demetrius \\u201cThe Greek\\u201d Havanas - the original members of \\u201cTexas Blood \\u2018n\\u2019 Guts\\u201d karate in the Dallas area.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Master Sosa is a passionate trainer who has amassed several prestigious accolades in Martial Arts tournaments including \\u201cThe Golden Greek\\u201d which is the highest award given by the Amateur Organization of Karate. Master Sosa was also honored with the Positive Coaching Alliance\\u2019s Double-Goal Coaching Award, awarded to coaches who implement positive life skills, work ethic and drive into their students training.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In 2010 Master Sosa started North Texas Martial Arts (NTMA), which ultimately joined Freddie Poole Martial Arts in 2015.<\\/p>\"}},\"30\":{\"type\":\"staff\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"62\"],\"staffName\":\"Jayda Clayton\",\"staffTitle\":\"Instructor, 2nd degree black belt\",\"body\":\"<p>Jayda Clayton, a 2nd degree black belt, began her training in January 2007 at the ripe old age of 4. A prodigy of Master Steven Sosa, Jayda received her yellow and brown belts in 2007 and 2009, respectively. At age 7, Jayda became Master Sosa\\u2019s first and youngest student to receive her black belt. Jayda has competed in numerous local, state and national karate competitions and won over 60 trophies in sparring and kata competitions with over 40 of them being first place positions.<\\/p>\"}},\"31\":{\"type\":\"staff\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"44\"],\"staffName\":\"Westin Poole\",\"staffTitle\":\"Instructor, 3rd degree black belt\",\"body\":\"<p>Westin Poole\\u2019s love for karate kicked in as a kid when began training in martial arts at the age of 6. By 2009, Westin was a certified 1st degree black belt and has no plans of slowing down. He has been teaching for almost eight years and enjoys working with children. The mission behind his teaching is inspiring his students to reach their goals and see the benefits of their hard work.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"65\":{\"type\":\"staff\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":\"\",\"staffName\":\"Vanny Boon\",\"staffTitle\":\"Instructor, 5th degree black belt, Saekson Muay Thai \",\"body\":\"<p>Master Vanny Boon is a certified 5th degree black belt skilled in various forms of martial arts including Taekwondo Do, Muay Thai, Brazilian Jiu jitsu and Boxing. Master Boon\\u2019s passion and experience for martial arts began when he started training at the age of 5 and spans over 25 years; Master Boon trained under Grand Master Hong, Master Freddie Poole and Muay Thai world champion Saekson Janjira.<\\/p>\"}},\"66\":{\"type\":\"staff\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"48\"],\"staffName\":\"Johnny Rodriguez\",\"staffTitle\":\"Instructor, Machado black belt\",\"body\":\"<p>Professor Johnny Rodriguez is a highly skilled black belt in Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu with over 20 years of training in several martial art forms including Kenpo karate, Aikido, Judo and Muay Thai. Professor Rodriguez teaches workshops, self-defense seminars, and has previously worked in law enforcement. &nbsp;Professor Rodriguez actively coaches students in preparation for BJJ tournaments and MMA bouts and still competes in many Brazilian jiu-jitsu tournaments.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"67\":{\"type\":\"staff\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"49\"],\"staffName\":\"Gerardo Mulas\",\"staffTitle\":\"Instructor, Certified Personal Trainer, Yoga\",\"body\":\"<p>Gerardo Mulas is a certified personal trainer, yoga and martial arts expert whose mission is educating students the benefits of fitness and health and wellness goals. Gerardo specializes in sports performance, weight loss, injury rehabilitation, stress relief, nutritional counseling and meal planning. Gerardo has over two decades of professional and collegiate athletics under his belt, along with extensive training in kickboxing, boxing and grappling.<\\/p>\"}},\"68\":{\"type\":\"staff\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"50\"],\"staffName\":\"Randy Stem\",\"staffTitle\":\"Instructor, 5th degree black belt, fitness trainer \",\"body\":\"<p>Randy Stem is a 5th degree black belt trained in Karate, Kickboxing, and Judo and currently in Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu. Randy studied under the teachings of Allen Steen, widely recognized as the \'Father of American Taekwondo\', and has over 45 years of experience mastering martial arts. Randy strongly encourages his students to build a firm foundation in martial arts early on by focusing on the development of basic fundamental motor skills and concepts.<\\/p>\"}},\"69\":{\"type\":\"staff\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"43\"],\"staffName\":\"Sovandy Om\",\"staffTitle\":\"Instructor, 5th degree black belt\",\"body\":\"<p>Master Sovandy Om is a 5th degree black belt, kickboxing fitness certified trainer and a FPMA student favorite. Master Om has trained extensively in Tae Kwon Do, MMA, Gymnastic, as well as Crossfit. Along with a passion for martial arts, Master Om has an even bigger passion for fitness. Master Om works tirelessly with helping the students execute proper technique to achieve the maximum benefits, as well as helping students reach and exceed their fitness goals.<\\/p>\"}},\"70\":{\"type\":\"staff\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"46\"],\"staffName\":\"Alex Garcia\",\"staffTitle\":\"Instructor, 2nd degree black belt\",\"body\":\"<p>Alex Garcia is a 2nd degree black belt in Tae Kwon Do who gravitated towards the world of martial arts at the age of 4. Alex soon began training to develop and perfect his skills for martial arts and became a student at Freddie Poole\'s Martial Arts at the age of 10. Within 2 years, Alex\\u2019s dedication transformed him into an avid competitor, in which Alex received several 1st place wins in state martial arts championships.<\\/p>\"}},\"71\":{\"type\":\"staff\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"45\"],\"staffName\":\"Nathan Bagby\",\"staffTitle\":\"Instructor, 3rd degree black belt, Muay Thai \",\"body\":\"<p>Nathanael \\u201cNathan\\u201d Bagby is a 3rd degree black belt and an accomplished Muay Thai fighter and instructor. Nathan first became interested and started training in martial arts at the age of 8, and in the past 25 years, has trained in Isshinryu Karate, Eskrima, Tae Kwon Do, American Kickboxing, Brazilian Jiu Jitsu, Close Quarter Combat, Boxing, and Muay Thai. &nbsp;Nathan has gone on to compete in several amateur and professional kickboxing and Muay Thai bouts.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"72\":{\"type\":\"staff\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":\"\",\"staffName\":\"Mike Rose\",\"staffTitle\":\"Instructor, Machado black belt \",\"body\":\"<p>Mike Rose has over 25 years of martial arts training, competition, and teaching experience in both Judo and Brazilian Jiu Jitsu. Mike started training in Judo in 1992, when he received his black belt. In 1998, under the teachings of Greg Nelson, Mike began training in Brazilian Jiu Jitsu and received his blue belt in 1999 and his black belt in 2009.<\\/p>\"}}},\"4\":\"\",\"3\":\"\"}}', '2016-06-15 02:55:56', '2016-06-15 02:55:56', 'ce165510-e7bd-49e9-ab3b-fde9cfbe64dc'),
 ('57', '73', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"About Freddie\",\"slug\":\"about-freddie\",\"postDate\":1465959376,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"5\":\"\",\"4\":\"\",\"3\":\"\"}}', '2016-06-15 02:56:16', '2016-06-15 02:56:16', '1193974d-8afa-4cae-8beb-e704932e2c26'),
 ('58', '73', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"About Freddie\",\"slug\":\"about-freddie\",\"postDate\":1465959360,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"5\",\"fields\":{\"5\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"secondaryHero\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"About Freddie\",\"body\":\"<p>Freddie Poole began martial arts training in 1981, at the age of seven years old. He began studying at Southwest Karate Academy under Demetrius \\u201cGolden Greek\\u201d Havanas. Southwest Karate Academy produced some of the best martial arts champions and competitors in the world, at that time. The 80\\u2019s were the tail end of the \\u201cTexas Blood and Guts\\u201d era of martial arts. The lineage began with Jhoon Rhee and his first black belt was Allen Steen. Steen went on to train many black belts and students and Texas was known for producing some of the best fighters in the country. Tim Kirby, Billye Jackson, Raymond McCallum, Santae Wilson Jr. and Cliff Thomas were some of the world-class competitors who had influence over Poole\\u2019s training and development.<\\/p>\",\"contactButton\":\"1\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#000000\",\"backgroundImage\":[\"36\"],\"mapTitle\":\"\",\"mapContent\":\"\",\"mapAddress\":\"\",\"flexibleArea\":\"\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"oneColumn\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"\",\"body\":\"<h3>As a young brown belt, Poole began teaching at Sun Belt Karate Academy by assisting younger and lower ranking students with warm-ups, kick punch technique and forms. It was not uncommon to see Poole leading an adult class at 12 years old.<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Poole received his 1st degree black belt in 1986, under Tim Kirby, Billye Jackson and Raymond McCallum. Poole competed in the AOK and was a top ranked competitor in forms and fighting for many years as a junior competitor.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Poole began training with long time friend and kickboxing champion Guy Mezger in 1993. Poole began honing his boxing and kickboxing skills with Mezger, Billye Jackson, Santae Wilson Jr. and Coach Charles Brown and went on to win a national title in 1997, which earned a spot on the US National Kickboxing team.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Poole\\u2019s boxing experience comes from training with some of the best coaches in the business. Phil Sawyer and Olympic Boxing Bronze medalist Charles Brown have influenced Poole in his boxing training, as well as Golden Gloves Champion Alex Andrade.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Poole has several years of Muay Thai experience, training with Francisco Sanchez of New World Combat, as well as World Muay Thai champion and MMA veteran Pete Spratt and Muay Thai champion Jason House.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Poole\\u2019s Judo experience comes from training with Master Vince Tamura and Judo Black Belt Rico Castro.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Poole currently trains under the tutelage of 8th degree Brazilian Jiu Jitsu master, Carlos Machado, where he holds a brown belt and is a proud affiliate of Machado Jiu Jitsu. Poole has also trained with many talented Brazilian Jiu Jitsu black belts including Kenny McClure, Jeff Sawyer, Rico Castro and Taryn Douglas.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Poole has competed all over the United States and internationally in Europe, winning a KICK International title in 2004 along with many team karate titles from 1999-2004. Poole also fought for Team Texas in Chuck Norris\\u2019s televised fight league, The World Combat League.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Poole has taken his vast knowledge of martial arts and created a well-rounded training system for all ages. Freddie Poole\\u2019s Martial Arts is the most balanced martial arts training system, combining traditional training elements with practical real world application. By integrating both of these elements into one system, one can truly train in mixed martial arts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Since opening its doors in 2004, Freddie Poole\'s Martial Arts has been impacting thousands&nbsp;of&nbsp;lives in the community. Our friendly staff looks forward each day to helping our students achieve their goals. Although standards are set high, each student at FPMA is evaluated on an individual basis to ensure progression on their own timeline. This approach ensures students achieve and&nbsp;earn rank on their own merit.&nbsp;We encourage our students to trust the process and enjoy it. Earning a black belt at FPMA is a once in a lifetime experience!<\\/p>\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#000000\",\"backgroundImage\":\"\"}}},\"4\":\"\",\"3\":\"\"}}', '2016-06-15 02:59:06', '2016-06-15 02:59:06', '3838e336-f31e-4539-bb84-8562d4965d81'),
