rthday celebrations. Decorations, music and food are welcome.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Interested in having your kid\\u2019s next birthday celebration at FPMA? <a href=\\\"tel:2143525425\\\">Give one of our locations a call<\\/a> for more information.<\\/p>\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#f5f5f5\",\"backgroundImage\":\"\"}},\"58\":{\"type\":\"oneColumn\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Special Events\",\"body\":\"<p><strong>FPMA is proud to announce our summer 2016 Karate Camp for kids.<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Karate Camp is designed for children ages 4-11 and provides the perfect summer getaway for kids interested in learning more about the many forms of martial art. Give you kids the opportunity to learn more about boosting leadership and teamwork skills, building and improving self confidence, self defense techniques, bully awareness as well as fun martial arts games and drills. Choose from 2 summer camp sessions only a $25 deposit required to reserve a spot.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>Reach out to a FPMA location for more details.<\\/p>\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#ffffff\",\"backgroundImage\":\"\"}},\"77\":{\"type\":\"oneColumn\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Women\\u2019s Self Defense Seminars\",\"body\":\"<p>Safety for our members is a major priority for us. FPMA offers self-defense classes for women to learn how to protect themselves and their loved ones from unexpected attacks. Join FPMA for one of our Women\\u2019s Self Defense Seminars in partnership with Not Dead Yet Apparel. Come get hands-on training as we demonstrate various self-defense techniques, learn empowering safety awareness and practices. Attendance is always free, but we accept donations of $25 or more to benefit a designated local non-profit organization. Take the first step by contacting one of our locations for more information.<\\/p>\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#f5f5f5\",\"backgroundImage\":\"\"}},\"78\":{\"type\":\"oneColumn\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Personal T