d for children ages 4 11 and provides the perfect summer getaway for kids interested in learning more about the many forms of martial art give you kids the opportunity to learn more about boosting leadership and teamwork skills building and improving self confidence self defense techniques bully awareness as well as fun martial arts games and drills choose from 2 summer camp sessions only a $25 deposit required to reserve a spot reach out to a fpma location for more details special events f5f5f5 safety for our members is a major priority for us fpma offers self defense classes for women to learn how to protect themselves and their loved ones from unexpected attacks join fpma for one of our women s self defense seminars in partnership with not dead yet apparel come get hands on training as we demonstrate various self defense techniques learn empowering safety awareness and practices attendance is always free but we accept donations of $25 or more to benefit a designated local non profit organization take the first step by contacting one of our locations for more information women s self defense seminars ffffff for the member who wants to learn the valuable techniques of martial arts outside of a group setting fpma offers specialized one on one training sessions members get individually structured personal instruction from one of our certified martial arts trainers training sessions are customized to benefit each student in any skill level from a novice student wanting a more personal experience or an advanced student preparing for competition contact one of our two dallas locations for more details personal training '),
